    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Alleghany County was named for the Allegheny Mountains, although it has a variant spelling. It was formed from Bath, Botetourt, and Monroe (West Virginia) Counties in 1822, and additional parts of Bath (1823) and Monroe (1843) were added. It area is 444 square miles, and the county seat is Covington. The former independent city of Clifton Forge reverted to the county in 2001. 
</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Alleghany County (Va.) Election Records, 1912-1947, consist of Rolls of Registered Voters for the town of Covington. 
</p>
    </scopecontent>
